WEBVTT

00:02.077 --> 00:08.899
♪

00:08.917 --> 00:14.680
♪

00:14.907 --> 00:20.244
♪

00:20.262 --> 00:24.023
♪

00:24.174 --> 00:26.433
[sighing]

00:26.585 --> 00:28.676
Sorry, everything's a
bit cold this morning.

00:28.771 --> 00:31.104
♪

00:31.198 --> 00:33.014
Thanks to jodi arias,

00:33.108 --> 00:34.682
I've had my life
threatened repeatedly,

00:34.777 --> 00:36.184
I've been attacked.

00:36.278 --> 00:38.853
I lost my job
and my family.

00:38.947 --> 00:42.857
For a while, I was the second
most-hated person in america.

00:42.951 --> 00:44.877
Marked by the devil herself.

00:47.439 --> 00:49.197
I think I'm okay
with a bit of cold.

00:49.291 --> 00:54.127
♪

00:54.280 --> 00:56.129
Let's start with your name.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.389
Donavan bering.

00:57.616 --> 01:00.634
D-o-n...

01:00.728 --> 01:05.122
A-v-a-n...

01:05.140 --> 01:11.070
♪

01:11.221 --> 01:12.738
[buzzing gate]

01:12.889 --> 01:14.573
[gate opening]

01:14.800 --> 01:20.637
♪

01:20.656 --> 01:25.066
♪

01:25.086 --> 01:26.159
<i> [donavan] I thought</i>
<i> being sent to jail</i>

01:26.253 --> 01:28.145
<i> Was my rock bottom.</i>

01:28.163 --> 01:30.756
♪

01:30.907 --> 01:33.483
<i> Now I know,</i>
<i> it wasn't even close.</i>

01:33.502 --> 01:39.264
♪

01:39.491 --> 01:45.270
♪

01:45.497 --> 01:48.181
<i> My plan was simple:</i>
<i> To survive.</i>

01:48.334 --> 01:50.925
<i> Take one day at a time</i>
<i> and just get through it.</i>

01:51.019 --> 01:52.927
<i> What wasn't in the plan?</i>

01:52.947 --> 01:55.114
<i> Falling in love.</i>

01:55.341 --> 01:57.950
[indistinct chatter]

01:58.101 --> 02:01.845
Watch out for rosie today.

02:01.864 --> 02:05.015
She's looking for
someone to punish.

02:05.108 --> 02:06.700
Well, she's always
been nice to me.

02:06.794 --> 02:09.035
Nobody's nice in here.

02:09.188 --> 02:11.946
You understand that, right?

02:11.966 --> 02:13.448
Okay.

02:13.467 --> 02:17.194
Babe, trust me.

02:17.287 --> 02:19.621
The ones that
aren't getting out,

02:19.715 --> 02:22.141
They've got nothing to lose.

02:22.368 --> 02:24.792
If I hadn't met you, I don't
think I would have made it.

02:24.812 --> 02:27.295
Yeah, but you did.

02:27.314 --> 02:30.632
And you will.

02:30.726 --> 02:35.045
Stay by my side,
I got you.

02:35.138 --> 02:37.214
Y'all hear what's
for lunch today?

02:37.307 --> 02:39.474
Prime ribs with baby
baked potatoes and

02:39.493 --> 02:41.568
Grilled asparagus.

02:41.720 --> 02:44.479
Or a chunk moldy bread
arpaio found in a dumpster.

02:44.498 --> 02:47.057
-[snickering]
-no.

02:47.150 --> 02:49.501
Lemon meringue pie
for dessert.

02:49.728 --> 02:51.486
Seriously, shut up.

02:51.505 --> 02:53.230
Or...

02:53.323 --> 02:56.750
-Chocolate fudge cake.
-Oh, yeah.

02:56.902 --> 02:58.752
-You see what you started?
-Yup.

02:58.904 --> 03:00.754
Warm raspberry crumble
with vanilla ice cream

03:00.906 --> 03:02.572
Just melting on top.

03:02.591 --> 03:05.350
-Ooh...
-That's the one.

03:05.502 --> 03:07.669
<i> Meeting tracy made</i>
<i> jail survivable.</i>

03:07.763 --> 03:10.004
<i> Now I- we-</i>
<i> had a new plan.</i>

03:10.024 --> 03:11.415
[door buzzing]

03:11.433 --> 03:13.650
<i> Do our time,</i>
<i> live happily ever after.</i>

03:16.588 --> 03:20.590
<i> And then, jodi arias</i>
<i> walked through the door.</i>

03:20.609 --> 03:22.517
[faint]
yeah...

03:22.611 --> 03:28.523
♪

03:28.617 --> 03:31.117
<i> None of us had</i>
<i> access to the news.</i>

03:31.212 --> 03:32.953
<i> While the rest of the world</i>
<i> knew her as the woman</i>

03:33.047 --> 03:36.030
<i> Who'd soon be on trial for</i>
<i> murdering her boyfriend,</i>

03:36.050 --> 03:38.199
<i> All we knew was she didn't</i>
<i> look like she belonged here.</i>

03:38.219 --> 03:40.293
Snitch.

03:40.446 --> 03:42.054
She won't last long.

03:42.205 --> 03:46.391
There's only one
empty bunk that way.

03:46.618 --> 03:48.134
Oh, hell no!

03:48.287 --> 03:51.471
Oh! Uh-oh!
[laughing]

03:51.623 --> 03:53.548
[indistinct chatter]

03:53.642 --> 03:59.220
♪ [suspenseful] ♪

03:59.314 --> 04:01.481
[guard]
brown... Brown!

04:01.633 --> 04:04.058
There's no way I'm
bunking with a snitch!

04:04.152 --> 04:06.653
-Get out!
-Hey!

04:06.747 --> 04:08.638
This ain't summer camp,
brown.

04:08.657 --> 04:10.415
You don't get to choose
who you bunk with.

04:10.642 --> 04:14.160
♪

04:14.313 --> 04:16.480
You want to get written up?

04:16.498 --> 04:19.240
♪

04:19.260 --> 04:21.151
[book hits to the floor]

04:21.169 --> 04:26.490
♪

04:26.508 --> 04:29.268
♪

04:29.495 --> 04:31.828
[snickering]

04:31.847 --> 04:38.668
♪

04:38.687 --> 04:42.339
♪

04:42.357 --> 04:43.690
Hey!

04:43.784 --> 04:46.601
Got a new girlfriend,
brown?

04:46.620 --> 04:48.862
-[lip smacking]
-[laughing]

04:48.956 --> 04:54.534
[indistinct heckling]

04:54.686 --> 04:55.519
I guess they're not
even trying to

04:55.612 --> 04:57.796
Disguise
snitches anymore.

04:57.947 --> 05:00.040
God, it's like dropping
a baby bunny

05:00.192 --> 05:02.301
Into a coyotes' den.

05:05.622 --> 05:07.639
I know, right.

05:12.371 --> 05:16.039
A snitch can get
your charges upped,

05:16.058 --> 05:17.799
Get you sent
to the hole.

05:17.893 --> 05:19.059
But we haven't
done anything.

05:19.153 --> 05:21.135
It doesn't matter!

05:21.229 --> 05:23.805
♪

05:23.824 --> 05:26.232
Never forget
where you are.

05:26.385 --> 05:28.718
I won't, I promise.

05:28.737 --> 05:33.832
♪

05:34.059 --> 05:40.747
♪

05:40.841 --> 05:42.841
[buzzer]

05:45.087 --> 05:49.072
♪

05:49.165 --> 05:51.499
[sighing]

05:51.593 --> 05:57.004
♪

05:57.099 --> 06:03.528
♪

06:03.680 --> 06:05.589
Goodnight.

06:05.607 --> 06:11.761
♪

06:11.780 --> 06:17.934
♪

06:17.953 --> 06:21.938
♪

06:22.031 --> 06:25.384
[echoing footsteps
in distance]

06:25.611 --> 06:30.447
♪

06:30.465 --> 06:34.467
♪

06:34.561 --> 06:37.454
Did she say anything?

06:37.472 --> 06:39.472
What is she doing
in there all day?

06:39.566 --> 06:41.641
Drawing, writing.

06:41.793 --> 06:44.310
"dear diary, I'm starting
to reconsider

06:44.405 --> 06:46.554
My life as a snitch."

06:46.648 --> 06:50.150
I know how we can
find out for sure.

06:50.302 --> 06:52.411
Ask her to do
something illegal.

06:52.638 --> 06:57.974
♪

06:57.993 --> 07:03.588
♪

07:03.815 --> 07:05.982
♪

07:06.075 --> 07:08.168
So you never
thought about it?

07:08.262 --> 07:10.595
Tattoos?

07:10.822 --> 07:13.748
You'd be good at it.

07:13.767 --> 07:17.084
-Well, how would we-
-there are ways.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.179
You in?

07:19.331 --> 07:21.940
[echoing footsteps
in the distance]

07:22.091 --> 07:24.192
Can I do the
first one on you?

07:27.948 --> 07:30.282
Sure.

07:35.530 --> 07:37.622
♪

07:37.849 --> 07:39.106
<i> Getting your hands on</i>
<i> the stuff you need</i>

07:39.126 --> 07:42.185
<i> To do jail tattoos is easy.</i>

07:42.204 --> 07:44.296
<i> But tattooing is a</i>
<i> major infraction,</i>

07:44.523 --> 07:49.283
<i> Right up there with</i>
<i> doing drugs or fighting.</i>

07:49.377 --> 07:51.452
<i> If you're caught, you could</i>
<i> lose all your privileges</i>

07:51.546 --> 07:53.955
<i> And end up in solitary.</i>

07:53.974 --> 07:56.199
<i> No snitch would</i>
<i> take the risk.</i>

07:56.218 --> 08:02.555
♪

08:02.649 --> 08:04.298
[effort grunting]

08:04.318 --> 08:06.710
You need it to be
a fine powder.

08:06.728 --> 08:09.154
♪

08:09.381 --> 08:12.065
-Thanks.
-For what?

08:12.159 --> 08:15.643
Trusting me to do this.

08:15.662 --> 08:19.239
I felt so alone coming here,
this means...

08:19.333 --> 08:21.983
It means a lot.

08:22.077 --> 08:25.912
♪

08:26.006 --> 08:32.827
[rattling & footsteps]

08:32.921 --> 08:35.755
♪

08:35.849 --> 08:38.241
[footsteps fading]

08:38.260 --> 08:42.078
♪

08:42.097 --> 08:47.600
♪

08:47.694 --> 08:50.511
Now, shampoo.

08:50.605 --> 08:54.032
♪

08:54.259 --> 08:56.426
Just a drop.

08:56.444 --> 08:58.444
♪

08:58.539 --> 09:00.372
[whispering]
alright.

09:00.599 --> 09:05.710
♪

09:05.937 --> 09:08.880
You know what happens if
you get caught, right?

09:09.107 --> 09:15.220
♪

09:15.447 --> 09:21.134
♪

09:21.228 --> 09:27.232
[jodi humming]

09:27.459 --> 09:29.459
[buzzer]

09:29.552 --> 09:34.130
[cell door closing & latching]

09:34.149 --> 09:40.303
♪

09:40.322 --> 09:46.233
♪

09:46.328 --> 09:51.981
♪

09:52.000 --> 09:57.596
♪

09:57.823 --> 10:00.599
♪

10:00.750 --> 10:04.344
Can I ask you a question?

10:04.438 --> 10:06.253
You mean "the" question?

10:06.348 --> 10:08.589
How'd I end up here?

10:08.683 --> 10:11.759
You don't have to answer.

10:11.778 --> 10:14.520
Same as everybody.

10:14.673 --> 10:17.006
Bad choices.

10:17.025 --> 10:21.845
♪

10:21.938 --> 10:23.938
I was with a guy who
tied somebody up,

10:24.032 --> 10:27.700
Beat him,
left him for dead.

10:27.853 --> 10:30.295
I thought he was
gonna kill me too.

10:30.446 --> 10:32.297
I was high and...

10:32.524 --> 10:34.357
I don't trust cops.

10:34.450 --> 10:36.283
[sighing]

10:36.378 --> 10:40.029
I got charged
like I did it.

10:40.123 --> 10:45.551
I'm not going home
for a long time.

10:45.646 --> 10:48.963
And your... Girlfriend?

10:48.982 --> 10:50.798
Did you know her before?

10:50.817 --> 10:53.801
No, met here...

10:53.820 --> 10:55.728
Day she arrived.

10:55.881 --> 10:58.472
And her bad choice?

10:58.492 --> 11:00.825
Ah...

11:00.977 --> 11:03.736
She trusted somebody that
burned a business down

11:03.889 --> 11:06.222
For insurance money.

11:06.315 --> 11:08.908
She found out about it,
didn't snitch.

11:09.060 --> 11:10.985
So, they put in her
in maximum security?

11:11.004 --> 11:12.395
She's from alaska.

11:12.488 --> 11:15.840
They thought she
was a flight risk.

11:16.067 --> 11:19.419
I'm so sorry for what
you've both gone through.

11:19.513 --> 11:21.513
It doesn't seem fair.

11:21.664 --> 11:22.906
What about you?

11:22.999 --> 11:25.758
I'm not supposed
to talk about it.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.927
Is this hurting?

11:28.021 --> 11:29.595
It looks like it would.

11:29.690 --> 11:32.248
It's fine.

11:32.267 --> 11:38.588
♪

11:38.606 --> 11:41.774
♪

11:41.868 --> 11:44.703
There was so much blood.

11:44.930 --> 11:50.208
♪

11:50.435 --> 11:55.863
♪

11:55.957 --> 12:03.221
♪

12:03.448 --> 12:06.040
Sorry...

12:06.059 --> 12:09.969
It's just that...

12:10.063 --> 12:14.733
Travis, my boyfriend...

12:14.884 --> 12:18.236
He was murdered.

12:18.387 --> 12:20.296
Stabbed and shot
right in front of me.

12:20.315 --> 12:26.244
♪

12:26.395 --> 12:28.654
What do you think so far?

12:28.749 --> 12:30.915
Um... [clearing throat]

12:31.067 --> 12:33.084
You'll get better
with practice.

12:33.236 --> 12:34.827
[laughing]

12:34.921 --> 12:37.088
It'll be great
when it's done.

12:37.240 --> 12:39.758
Trust me.

12:39.985 --> 12:42.652
[indistinct chatter]

12:42.670 --> 12:47.840
♪

12:47.934 --> 12:49.434
[whispering]
hey...

12:49.661 --> 12:51.936
I finally got a crystal
they can't take from me.

12:52.163 --> 12:56.165
♪

12:56.184 --> 12:59.110
♪

12:59.262 --> 13:01.279
So, she's okay?

13:01.506 --> 13:04.431
Yeah, I think so...

13:04.526 --> 13:10.288
♪

13:10.515 --> 13:14.517
♪

13:14.536 --> 13:16.352
Hey!

13:16.371 --> 13:22.634
♪

13:22.785 --> 13:25.470
This is donavan.

13:25.621 --> 13:27.472
I'm jodi.

13:29.810 --> 13:33.386
Initials of my
niece and nephew.

13:33.480 --> 13:37.482
And now I appreciate
the skill those took.

13:37.633 --> 13:39.800
I have another one on my
back and a buddha on my leg.

13:39.820 --> 13:42.303
-You're buddhist?
-Since I was 22.

13:42.322 --> 13:44.047
I asked my mom
to send me books.

13:44.140 --> 13:45.731
There's one about
buddhism on my list.

13:45.826 --> 13:48.234
I'll share it with you.

13:48.328 --> 13:49.810
I'm actually mormon now.

13:49.904 --> 13:51.904
I converted for my
boyfriend, travis.

13:51.998 --> 13:55.816
For me, really, for us.

13:55.910 --> 13:58.485
But I'm fascinated
by all religions.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.505
Tracy's wiccan.

14:00.656 --> 14:02.231
When I was younger, I had
a boyfriend who was wiccan,

14:02.325 --> 14:05.068
So it was a big
part of my life too.

14:05.161 --> 14:08.346
What I love most both about
buddhism and wicca

14:08.497 --> 14:10.497
Is the emphasis on nature.

14:10.517 --> 14:12.075
When you strip
everything else away,

14:12.168 --> 14:14.243
All the stuff that
doesn't matter,

14:14.337 --> 14:17.522
That's what we
have left, nature.

14:17.749 --> 14:20.917
And love...

14:20.935 --> 14:23.419
Sorry, sometimes I talk
too much about subjects

14:23.438 --> 14:25.363
I'm really
passionate about.

14:25.590 --> 14:27.940
That's okay.

14:28.034 --> 14:30.610
I think it's beautiful that
you two found each other.

14:30.762 --> 14:34.521
Here, of all places.

14:34.541 --> 14:36.782
I think it was
anne frank who wrote,

14:36.935 --> 14:38.768
"I don't think of
all the misery,

14:38.786 --> 14:40.461
But of the beauty that
still remains."

14:43.124 --> 14:48.111
♪

14:48.204 --> 14:49.888
Does anybody want this?
I don't need it.

14:50.039 --> 14:52.056
I'll take it.

14:52.283 --> 14:56.227
♪

14:56.454 --> 15:00.123
♪

15:00.141 --> 15:01.791
<i> Of course we liked her.</i>

15:01.809 --> 15:04.127
<i> She was smart,</i>
<i> she was interesting.</i>

15:04.145 --> 15:06.812
<i> And she wasn't like</i>
<i> anybody else we'd ever met.</i>

15:06.907 --> 15:08.481
"pernicious."

15:08.633 --> 15:11.159
You realize none of this
is sinking in, right?

15:13.729 --> 15:16.915
Okay well, how about a
word from yesterday then?

15:17.066 --> 15:19.584
"duress."

15:19.811 --> 15:22.569
We're being forced to
learn words under duress.

15:22.589 --> 15:26.907
[laughing] see?

15:26.927 --> 15:28.909
"pernicious."

15:28.929 --> 15:30.911
No clue.

15:30.931 --> 15:34.490
"causing great harm or
damage in a way that

15:34.583 --> 15:39.270
Is not easily
seen or noticed."

15:39.497 --> 15:41.180
Huh.

15:41.274 --> 15:43.274
Let's do another one.

15:45.445 --> 15:50.264
[inaudible conversation]

15:50.283 --> 15:52.191
[crying]
mom, I just miss you...

15:52.285 --> 15:55.436
Thank you so much.

15:55.530 --> 15:57.196
What was that about?

15:57.290 --> 15:59.682
Nothing.

15:59.701 --> 16:01.275
She needed to
call her family,

16:01.369 --> 16:02.685
But she couldn't afford it.

16:02.778 --> 16:03.869
You put money on
her phone account?

16:03.964 --> 16:05.705
Do you even know her?

16:05.857 --> 16:08.132
She needed her mom.

16:08.359 --> 16:12.545
♪

16:12.639 --> 16:15.640
There's this one or...?

16:18.703 --> 16:20.645
I want something to
symbolize my love for tracy.

16:25.543 --> 16:27.543
My boyfriend travis
used to do that.

16:27.636 --> 16:29.821
He wouldn't even
have to say anything.

16:30.048 --> 16:35.551
♪

16:35.570 --> 16:39.980
♪

16:40.000 --> 16:42.558
He'd just look
at me and I knew.

16:42.577 --> 16:45.336
♪

16:45.563 --> 16:47.897
More than anything else,
that's what I miss.

16:47.915 --> 16:54.495
♪

16:54.514 --> 16:59.575
He was murdered.

16:59.668 --> 17:04.522
The police think I did it,
that's why I'm here.

17:04.749 --> 17:08.509
As if I could ever
kill somebody I loved.

17:08.528 --> 17:11.154
Crazy, right?

17:13.091 --> 17:18.202
[indistinct chatter]

17:18.354 --> 17:19.612
<i> Not everybody liked her.</i>

17:19.706 --> 17:21.688
Hey...

17:21.708 --> 17:23.449
They're making a
plan to get jodi.

17:23.601 --> 17:25.859
Who?

17:25.879 --> 17:29.863
Who do you think?

17:29.883 --> 17:31.457
Today.

17:31.551 --> 17:34.385
What am I going to do?

17:34.537 --> 17:36.554
[clicking tongue]

17:36.781 --> 17:40.449
♪

17:40.468 --> 17:43.877
♪

17:43.897 --> 17:46.806
You want to
get to arias...

17:46.958 --> 17:49.901
You gotta go
through me.

17:50.128 --> 17:52.978
Everybody got that?!

17:53.073 --> 17:55.722
Got it?

17:55.817 --> 17:59.802
♪ [suspenseful] ♪

17:59.895 --> 18:01.728
Do you...

18:01.823 --> 18:04.307
[shouting] hear me?!

18:04.325 --> 18:10.755
♪

18:10.982 --> 18:15.167
♪

18:15.320 --> 18:21.099
[indistinct chatter]

18:21.326 --> 18:25.085
<i> During the day, jodi</i>
<i> stuck to us like glue.</i>

18:25.179 --> 18:27.939
<i> But nights were another story.</i>

18:28.090 --> 18:30.757
[cell door unlatching
and opening]

18:30.777 --> 18:33.111
[buzzer]

18:33.262 --> 18:36.263
[cell door closing
& latching]

18:36.282 --> 18:40.618
[fading footsteps]

18:45.016 --> 18:49.518
Hey, where were you?

18:49.612 --> 18:55.282
I've been doing
tv interviews.

18:55.376 --> 18:57.877
It's going to help my case.

18:57.971 --> 19:01.864
If people get to know me,
see that I'm smart and

19:01.957 --> 19:04.976
Articulate, hear my
side of the story.

19:05.127 --> 19:06.385
[scoffing]

19:06.537 --> 19:09.981
Yeah, I'm sure there are
hundreds of women

19:10.208 --> 19:13.559
Who would love to tell their
side of their story.

19:13.653 --> 19:17.804
[whispering]
why you?

19:17.824 --> 19:20.825
It's not my fault that
people are interested in me.

19:20.976 --> 19:23.661
[sighing]
be careful.

19:23.888 --> 19:26.405
Always.

19:26.499 --> 19:32.395
[humming]

19:32.488 --> 19:34.914
<i> Jodi did endless interviews.</i>

19:35.008 --> 19:38.009
<i> While everybody on the</i>
<i> outside was seeing this...</i>

19:38.236 --> 19:40.403
I'd be shaking in my boots
right now if I had to

19:40.421 --> 19:43.347
Answer to god for such
a heinous crime.

19:43.574 --> 19:44.998
I'm very grateful that
this is one thing

19:45.092 --> 19:47.426
I'll never have
to answer to.

19:47.520 --> 19:50.746
I did not kill travis.

19:50.839 --> 19:52.673
<i> All we were</i>
<i> seeing was this...</i>

19:52.692 --> 19:55.100
[tv] ...Sprucing up
any dish.

19:55.253 --> 19:58.011
And these pastries will
be the apple of your eye.

19:58.105 --> 20:01.106
♪

20:01.259 --> 20:06.537
[humming
'amazing grace']

20:06.689 --> 20:12.785
[humming]

20:12.879 --> 20:18.549
[humming]

20:18.701 --> 20:24.296
[humming]

20:24.449 --> 20:27.708
I'm gonna call you
songbird from now on.

20:27.802 --> 20:30.803
That's what you
remind me of.

20:30.955 --> 20:34.139
Goodnight, songbird.

20:34.234 --> 20:37.476
Goodnight.

20:37.570 --> 20:41.647
[singing] amazing grace,

20:41.799 --> 20:47.136
How sweet the sound.

20:47.154 --> 20:55.828
That saved a wretch like me.

20:55.922 --> 21:00.165
I once was lost...

21:00.260 --> 21:06.005
But now am found.

21:06.157 --> 21:14.497
Was blind,
but now I see.

21:14.515 --> 21:19.351
'twas grace that brought...
My heart...

21:19.445 --> 21:20.778
<i> Until my dying day,</i>

21:21.005 --> 21:24.673
<i> That song will never</i>
<i> bring me comfort.</i>

21:24.767 --> 21:26.842
<i> Thanks to jodi, it's burned</i>
<i> in my memory as</i>

21:26.861 --> 21:31.347
<i> Something I was too naive to</i>
<i> realize at the time...</i>

21:31.365 --> 21:34.458
<i> The sound of the devil</i>
<i> singing us to sleep.</i>

21:34.685 --> 21:41.132
[singing] ...How precious
did that grace appear

21:41.283 --> 21:47.305
The hour I first believed.

21:51.719 --> 21:55.980
♪

21:56.131 --> 21:57.798
<i> [donavan]</i>
<i> prison crushes you.</i>

21:57.892 --> 21:59.708
<i> Makes you less</i>
<i> than you are.</i>

21:59.727 --> 22:01.544
<i> But tracy gave me hope.</i>

22:01.637 --> 22:04.046
<i> Hope I could survive it.</i>

22:04.065 --> 22:06.640
<i> We were a team</i>
<i> facing it together.</i>

22:06.734 --> 22:09.234
♪

22:09.387 --> 22:11.720
[door opening &
buzzer]

22:11.739 --> 22:16.909
♪

22:17.061 --> 22:19.152
<i> It didn't take long for us</i>
<i> to realize that there was</i>

22:19.246 --> 22:21.897
<i> One set of rules</i>
<i> for jodi arias,</i>

22:21.916 --> 22:23.657
<i> And one set of rules for</i>
<i> everybody else.</i>

22:23.751 --> 22:26.159
[door latching
& buzzer]

22:26.253 --> 22:29.905
♪

22:29.924 --> 22:31.515
This is gonna look
so good, donovan.

22:31.742 --> 22:33.166
Can't wait.

22:33.186 --> 22:35.911
Guard.

22:36.004 --> 22:39.690
[donavan clearing throat]

22:39.917 --> 22:42.676
This ain't your cell,
brown, clear out.

22:42.695 --> 22:45.363
Where were you yesterday,
officer bricker?

22:45.514 --> 22:47.180
We missed you.

22:47.274 --> 22:50.593
You need to wrap
this up in here.

22:50.686 --> 22:55.264
Since you asked so nicely.

22:55.357 --> 22:57.333
Love the new haircut,
by the way.

23:01.881 --> 23:04.940
[laughing]

23:04.959 --> 23:11.113
♪

23:11.132 --> 23:15.226
♪

23:15.377 --> 23:18.378
[gasping]

23:18.398 --> 23:21.065
There are benefits to being
nice to them, you know.

23:21.216 --> 23:22.566
You can do what you want.

23:22.793 --> 23:23.976
I'm no badge bunny.

23:24.070 --> 23:25.236
So you don't
want one then?

23:25.463 --> 23:27.630
Nope.

23:27.723 --> 23:30.241
[singing] chocolate
chip cookies.

23:30.468 --> 23:34.136
Chocolatey chip in
tracy's tummy tum.

23:34.155 --> 23:39.308
♪

23:39.326 --> 23:44.404
♪

23:44.424 --> 23:46.498
-Mm!
-Mmm!

23:46.651 --> 23:51.595
-My god.
-Mm, right?

23:51.822 --> 23:53.413
The lady who lived
next door to us

23:53.507 --> 23:57.268
Made these when
I was little.

23:57.419 --> 24:02.440
She'd see me sitting
outside and call me over.

24:02.667 --> 24:05.684
Sometimes it was all
I had to eat that day.

24:05.778 --> 24:08.687
Where was your family?

24:08.839 --> 24:11.765
Ah... I lived with
my grandmother.

24:11.784 --> 24:14.785
Yeah...

24:14.937 --> 24:17.270
She hated me.

24:17.290 --> 24:19.014
Or...

24:19.107 --> 24:21.125
[sighing]
that's how it felt.

24:21.352 --> 24:25.204
I'm sure she didn't.

24:25.298 --> 24:29.950
My grandmother carried around
a wooden spoon with her.

24:29.969 --> 24:34.379
She would beat me with
it every single day.

24:34.532 --> 24:36.640
[sniffling]

24:36.792 --> 24:38.717
Sometimes she would
beat me so hard...

24:38.811 --> 24:41.220
It would break in half.

24:41.314 --> 24:44.723
Then she'd use the belt.

24:44.875 --> 24:47.710
I had so many bruises and
welts on my body that

24:47.728 --> 24:49.545
I had to wear a
long-sleeved shirt and

24:49.638 --> 24:54.158
Pants to school
just to hide them.

24:54.385 --> 24:59.738
At the end of her life,
my grandmother apologized.

24:59.832 --> 25:04.393
I sat by her side for a week.

25:04.486 --> 25:07.396
She just kept saying it
over and over.

25:07.414 --> 25:13.919
♪

25:14.071 --> 25:15.829
There's not enough
apologies in this world

25:15.923 --> 25:20.017
For being a monster.

25:20.244 --> 25:22.502
[sniffling]

25:22.596 --> 25:26.857
♪

25:27.009 --> 25:28.917
I'm so sorry.

25:28.936 --> 25:33.847
♪

25:33.866 --> 25:37.017
I can't imagine.

25:37.111 --> 25:38.761
My parents weren't perfect,

25:38.854 --> 25:41.205
But my childhood was
pretty much ideal.

25:44.118 --> 25:47.452
♪

25:47.605 --> 25:49.788
You're such a
beautiful person.

25:49.882 --> 25:52.958
You didn't deserve that.

25:53.110 --> 25:54.943
Nobody does.

25:54.962 --> 26:00.206
♪

26:00.301 --> 26:03.561
Anybody that
hurts a kid

26:03.788 --> 26:05.879
Deserves to suffer.

26:05.898 --> 26:09.549
Every last one of them.

26:09.569 --> 26:11.569
[door buzzer]

26:11.720 --> 26:14.797
[cell door closing
& latching]

26:14.815 --> 26:15.981
Well, I'm sure
the sugar will

26:16.133 --> 26:17.724
Help us sleep like
babies tonight.

26:17.743 --> 26:18.817
[tracy] yeah.

26:18.969 --> 26:21.561
Hey?

26:21.581 --> 26:23.563
I hope you dream of...

26:23.583 --> 26:26.158
Something better.

26:26.252 --> 26:29.235
Yeah, thanks.

26:29.330 --> 26:35.593
♪

26:35.744 --> 26:39.004
[jodi chewing]

26:39.156 --> 26:42.324
[indistinct chatter]

26:42.417 --> 26:44.768
Donavan has her
court case today.

26:44.995 --> 26:47.830
Judge will decide how
much longer she's here.

26:47.923 --> 26:50.015
What do you think
is going to happen?

26:50.167 --> 26:54.353
In my experience,
nothing good.

26:54.447 --> 26:56.855
She's so scared.

26:56.949 --> 26:58.765
I have to do something.

26:58.784 --> 27:02.453
She'll be fine.

27:02.604 --> 27:04.104
[sighing]

27:04.198 --> 27:06.957
If I could just
make her laugh,

27:07.109 --> 27:09.126
I know it would make
her feel better.

27:11.689 --> 27:14.022
Donovan!

27:14.116 --> 27:18.302
[cheering &
whistling continues]

27:36.489 --> 27:38.155
Brown, arias.

27:38.382 --> 27:40.807
Show's over.

27:40.826 --> 27:42.475
Arias!

27:42.495 --> 27:45.979
[chatter quiets]

27:45.998 --> 27:47.998
I love you more
than unicorns!

27:48.225 --> 27:49.649
[inaudible]

27:49.743 --> 27:52.411
[door buzzer &
door opening]

27:52.563 --> 27:55.005
[indistinct chatter]

27:55.232 --> 27:56.732
[jodi] don't worry.

27:56.750 --> 28:00.085
♪

28:00.237 --> 28:02.254
She doesn't
deserve to be here.

28:02.348 --> 28:04.256
But if she goes home...

28:04.408 --> 28:05.498
You don't want to lose her.

28:05.518 --> 28:08.260
I could be here
for ten years.

28:08.354 --> 28:10.354
I can't ask her to wait.

28:10.505 --> 28:12.764
I don't think you have to.

28:12.917 --> 28:15.859
She loves you
and you love her.

28:16.011 --> 28:19.345
It's worth doing whatever
it takes to hang on to that.

28:19.365 --> 28:20.680
Sure.

28:20.700 --> 28:23.367
Listen to me.

28:23.594 --> 28:26.019
You can't let anybody take
that love away from you.

28:26.038 --> 28:27.946
Ever.

28:28.040 --> 28:30.708
Thanks, songbird.

28:30.859 --> 28:33.118
And a sexy dance every
now and then never hurts.

28:33.270 --> 28:34.861
[snickering]

28:34.880 --> 28:37.530
Always happy to help.

28:37.624 --> 28:42.961
♪

28:43.113 --> 28:47.540
[indistinct chatter]

28:47.560 --> 28:49.801
Five months,
minus time served.

28:49.954 --> 28:51.061
The judge wished he
could give me less,

28:51.288 --> 28:52.378
Doesn't think I
should be here at all.

28:52.398 --> 28:54.732
Yeah, he's right.

28:54.959 --> 29:00.462
♪

29:00.481 --> 29:04.057
So, what, you could be out
of here in a couple weeks?

29:04.076 --> 29:07.135
I could.

29:07.154 --> 29:10.897
Hey look, it doesn't
matter where we are.

29:10.916 --> 29:13.233
We're still together.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.644
-I love you.
-I love you too.

29:15.662 --> 29:19.923
♪

29:20.150 --> 29:22.408
Sorry to interrupt.

29:22.428 --> 29:24.762
I had an idea.

29:24.989 --> 29:30.158
♪

29:30.177 --> 29:33.845
♪

29:33.998 --> 29:35.922
<i> It wasn't real...</i>

29:35.941 --> 29:37.941
You look so beautiful.

29:38.168 --> 29:41.520
<i> ...But it was as close as</i>
<i> we could get at the time.</i>

29:41.672 --> 29:44.448
<i> And it felt real to us.</i>

29:44.599 --> 29:49.027
Fate, karma and destiny
have brought

29:49.179 --> 29:52.848
Tracy and donavan
together in a marriage

29:52.941 --> 29:57.035
Of two faiths and two
beautiful souls.

29:57.129 --> 30:00.872
<i> We had no idea that the hand</i>
<i> that blessed our marriage</i>

30:00.966 --> 30:04.042
<i> Was the same hand that,</i>
<i> just five months earlier,</i>

30:04.194 --> 30:07.546
<i> Stabbed travis alexander</i>
<i> as many as 29 times,</i>

30:07.698 --> 30:10.641
<i> Shot him in the head, and</i>
<i> sliced his throat with so</i>

30:10.792 --> 30:14.269
<i> Much force that it just</i>
<i> about decapitated him.</i>

30:19.485 --> 30:24.880
♪ [eerie] ♪

30:24.898 --> 30:30.494
♪

30:30.721 --> 30:34.222
♪

30:34.316 --> 30:37.918
[gasping]

30:39.505 --> 30:41.746
You okay?

30:41.841 --> 30:46.176
Yeah, just,
weirdest dream.

30:46.328 --> 30:49.588
Hm, I get those a lot too.

30:49.740 --> 30:53.758
All I saw was you, alone...

30:53.911 --> 30:57.762
Like, wearing a white dress.

30:57.857 --> 31:00.173
Like floating.

31:00.192 --> 31:04.844
I mean, it was
beautiful, but...

31:04.864 --> 31:08.532
Something about it...

31:08.683 --> 31:14.204
It was a prophecy.

31:14.356 --> 31:16.281
What do you mean?

31:16.375 --> 31:18.876
If I'm found guilty,
I'm going to kill myself.

31:19.027 --> 31:22.045
Songbird!

31:22.272 --> 31:25.716
Don't worry about it,
no jury will convict me.

31:25.943 --> 31:31.704
♪

31:31.798 --> 31:34.616
♪

31:34.709 --> 31:40.898
[sighing]

31:43.310 --> 31:44.976
Hey, hey,
possible incoming.

31:45.070 --> 31:46.628
Who is it?

31:46.721 --> 31:47.979
It's the new guy, schmidt.

31:48.073 --> 31:50.890
Don't worry about him.

31:50.910 --> 31:53.652
Did you flash him?

31:53.804 --> 31:55.971
I can neither
confirm nor deny.

31:55.989 --> 31:59.157
[laughing]
oh my god.

31:59.251 --> 32:00.751
You're the worst.

32:00.902 --> 32:05.071
We do what we have to do.

32:05.090 --> 32:07.382
Mind if I sign my name to it?

32:09.595 --> 32:13.597
Um...

32:13.748 --> 32:16.224
I want you to have
something to remember me by.

32:20.588 --> 32:21.921
[sighing]

32:22.015 --> 32:24.666
Songbird,
please don't.

32:24.685 --> 32:28.261
♪

32:28.280 --> 32:31.281
I told the police everything
that happened that night.

32:31.508 --> 32:34.859
I was there when two
intruders broke in-

32:34.954 --> 32:38.121
One male, one female.

32:38.273 --> 32:42.125
Dressed in black,
wearing masks.

32:42.277 --> 32:45.611
[whispering]
I saw them kill travis.

32:45.631 --> 32:47.130
I thought they were
going to kill me too,

32:47.282 --> 32:49.024
But I got away.

32:49.042 --> 32:52.877
♪

32:53.030 --> 32:54.787
As long as I'm in here,
do you think they're even

32:54.807 --> 32:56.974
Bothering to look for
the real murderers?

32:57.201 --> 33:01.369
♪

33:01.388 --> 33:07.300
♪

33:07.319 --> 33:09.486
I just thought,
when I'm gone,

33:09.713 --> 33:12.897
At least my name will
still be with you.

33:12.992 --> 33:15.383
Maybe knowing I'm at peace
will bring you peace too.

33:15.402 --> 33:19.479
♪

33:19.498 --> 33:21.723
Never mind,
it's a silly idea.

33:21.742 --> 33:26.837
♪

33:27.064 --> 33:28.672
No...

33:28.823 --> 33:30.248
I mean...

33:30.342 --> 33:32.734
Sure, why not?

33:32.753 --> 33:38.331
♪

33:38.350 --> 33:40.166
<i> [donavan] when jodi tattooed</i>
<i> her name on tracy,</i>

33:40.260 --> 33:42.668
<i> It seemed innocent enough.</i>

33:42.763 --> 33:45.747
♪

33:45.766 --> 33:49.509
<i> Up until that day, the three</i>
<i> of us had been inseparable.</i>

33:49.603 --> 33:50.935
<i> That was about to change.</i>

33:51.030 --> 33:53.421
[screaming] no!

33:53.440 --> 33:54.531
Somebody reported
your relationship

33:54.758 --> 33:57.609
With donavan bering.
You know how this works.

33:57.703 --> 33:59.185
We have to separate you.

33:59.279 --> 34:03.022
This isn't right
and you know it!

34:03.042 --> 34:04.766
Please let her stay,
please.

34:04.859 --> 34:07.044
Arias, step outside,
step outside.

34:11.550 --> 34:12.698
What's happening!?

34:12.718 --> 34:14.125
They're moving
her to tower b.

34:14.278 --> 34:15.552
No!

34:15.779 --> 34:16.778
Don't make this harder
than necessary, brown.

34:16.871 --> 34:19.038
Let's go.

34:19.058 --> 34:21.892
This is bull!

34:22.119 --> 34:24.227
The one good thing
I have in my life.

34:24.379 --> 34:26.471
[effort grunting]

34:26.623 --> 34:28.065
Songbird,
you and donavan

34:28.216 --> 34:29.808
Have to take care
of each other.

34:29.960 --> 34:32.127
No, no, no, I can't
do this without you.

34:32.220 --> 34:33.978
-I love you.
-I love you too.

34:34.131 --> 34:34.979
It's gonna be okay,
it's gonna be okay.

34:35.074 --> 34:36.314
-Let's go.
-No!

34:36.466 --> 34:37.482
-Brown, let's go!
-I'm not going!

34:37.634 --> 34:40.243
-Let's go!
-Tracy!

34:40.395 --> 34:42.470
-Stay back!
-[groaning & sputtering]

34:42.489 --> 34:44.564
-Tracy!
-[taser buzzing]

34:44.583 --> 34:47.158
Tracy! Tracy!

34:47.311 --> 34:49.811
Tracy! Stop,
you're hurting her!

34:49.904 --> 34:52.314
Lock down,
back to your cells!

34:52.332 --> 34:56.742
♪

34:56.837 --> 35:01.489
♪

35:01.508 --> 35:03.934
♪

35:04.085 --> 35:07.178
[chatter] come on, you don't
want to get in trouble.

35:07.272 --> 35:09.164
[door buzzer]

35:09.182 --> 35:11.090
♪

35:11.110 --> 35:12.667
[door closing]

35:12.760 --> 35:14.853
<i> After tracy was moved</i>
<i> to solitary...</i>

35:14.947 --> 35:18.115
<i> Jodi was scared.</i>

35:18.342 --> 35:20.266
<i> So was I.</i>

35:20.360 --> 35:22.193
♪

35:22.287 --> 35:24.287
<i> Tracy kept us safe.</i>

35:24.439 --> 35:25.789
<i> And now, no matter</i>
<i> where we were,</i>

35:26.016 --> 35:29.126
<i> Locked down or not,</i>
<i> anything could happen.</i>

35:31.705 --> 35:33.021
<i> And there were</i>
<i> new arrivals</i>

35:33.039 --> 35:35.423
<i> Who had seen plenty</i>
<i> of jodi on tv.</i>

35:38.378 --> 35:40.545
<i> They figured they'd get</i>
<i> their 15 minutes of fame</i>

35:40.697 --> 35:42.622
<i> By being the one to</i>
<i> kill jodi arias.</i>

35:42.716 --> 35:44.699
[guard] take it
easy out there.

35:44.718 --> 35:48.645
♪

35:48.872 --> 35:50.205
<i> On the outside,</i>
<i> I may have looked like</i>

35:50.223 --> 35:52.315
<i> I could protect jodi.</i>

35:52.542 --> 35:55.152
<i> But on the inside,</i>
<i> I knew I couldn't.</i>

35:55.379 --> 36:00.064
♪

36:00.217 --> 36:02.642
[rustling]

36:02.736 --> 36:05.069
<i>And I missed</i>
<i> my wife.</i>

36:05.164 --> 36:07.647
[echoing footsteps]

36:07.741 --> 36:11.668
♪

36:11.895 --> 36:16.089
♪

36:18.568 --> 36:23.496
[indistinct chatter]

36:23.515 --> 36:24.664
I really don't want to
lose touch with you

36:24.683 --> 36:26.241
After you leave.

36:26.334 --> 36:28.351
Me either.

36:28.578 --> 36:30.854
Hey, remember that first
day when I met you?

36:31.081 --> 36:33.690
I knew you came into
my life for a reason.

36:33.917 --> 36:36.100
Our bond of sisterhood,
it makes me feel like

36:36.253 --> 36:39.437
I can survive anything.
That's all thanks to you.

36:39.589 --> 36:41.606
Me?

36:41.758 --> 36:43.033
When are you going to start
believing people

36:43.260 --> 36:47.037
When they tell you how
awesome you are?

36:47.264 --> 36:50.373
Hey, maybe you can help me
with my social media,

36:50.600 --> 36:52.709
So I can get the word
out about my innocence.

36:52.936 --> 36:54.953
I need somebody I trust
to help me with that.

36:55.047 --> 36:58.940
You know I trust you more
than anyone, even my family.

36:59.033 --> 37:00.884
Sure, whatever
you need, yeah.

37:01.111 --> 37:04.779
[indistinct chatter]

37:04.872 --> 37:06.539
[whispering]
I got a note from tracy.

37:06.558 --> 37:09.392
She told me to act out so
they put me in the hole too.

37:09.619 --> 37:10.876
You're not going
to do it, are you?

37:10.896 --> 37:13.879
-I have to.
-No, you don't.

37:13.899 --> 37:15.957
It's the last chance I have
to see her before I'm released.

37:15.976 --> 37:17.216
When I'm out,
I'll be on probation,

37:17.310 --> 37:18.793
